  "texts": [
    "Some had problems with missing background knowledge especially for historic celebrities like Margaret Thatcher or Edwin Moses due to their young age.",
    "Still, some of the subjectively trivial questions like relations between animal types resulted in surprising answers (e.g.",
    "donkey and zebra as an answer to \"A tiger relates to a wildcat like a horse relates to what?\" instead of pony).",
    "On the other hand, some of the questions that were rather controversial because they seem underspecified, were answered relatively homogeneously in the expected way.",
    "Especially age-related behaviour was only scarcely questioned and over 95% of participants agreed that children are more likely to eat ice cream than their grandparents and vice versa for cigarettes."
  ],
